quran[22]{c,v,t}:
  54,50,"And Our command is but once, like the twinkling of an eye."
  54,51,"And most surely We have annihilated your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>likes, so is there anyone to remind himself?"
  54,52,"And everything they have done is in the Books—"
  54,53,"for everything, small or large, is written down."
  54,54,"Indeed, the mindful<i class=""s"">(of God) </i>are amidst Gardens and rivers,"
  54,55,"in a seat of truth, in the presence of an Invincible King."
  55,1,"The All-Merciful"
  55,2,"taught the Recital{1}",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Qur’an which literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  55,3,"created man,"
  55,4,"and taught him clear expression."
  55,5,"The sun and the moon move according to plan,"
  55,6,"and the plants{1}and the trees prostrate themselves.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is najmwhich also means ‘star’; notice the suitability of the term which connects what is before it with what is after it.
  55,7,"And the sky—He raised it and set up the balance,"
  55,8,"so do<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>not exceed in the balance,"
  55,9,"but maintain the weights justly and do not fall short in the balance."
  55,10,"And the earth—He set it up for living creatures;"
  55,11,"in it are fruits and sheathed palm trees<span class=""h"">,</span>"
  55,12,"<span class=""h"">and grains<sup foot_note=""81252"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">in the blades, and fragrant plants</span>."
  55,13,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>disbelieve in{1}?",footnotes:1:The Qur’an is addressing the two types of responsible creatures: humans and jinn.
  55,14,"He created man from potter’s clay like pottery"
  55,15,"and created the unseen being{1}from a smokeless flame of fire.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is jānn(the singular of jinn), which is an unseen being that is accountable for its actions.
  55,16,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>disbelieve in?"
